[DOORBELL CHIMES]

07:46.767 --> 07:48.167
How you doing?

07:48.167 --> 07:51.534
I'm sorry, Kelly's
at her grandmother's.

07:51.534 --> 07:53.234
Actually, I'm looking
for Marcie Rhoades.

07:53.234 --> 07:55.701
She live here?

07:55.701 --> 07:57.200
Practically.

07:57.200 --> 07:59.767
Who wants to know?

07:59.767 --> 08:01.267
I'm Raul.

08:01.267 --> 08:02.868
You know, Zorro.

08:02.868 --> 08:07.801
Yeah, I'm Al.
You know, suspicious.

08:07.801 --> 08:09.300
Al? Al Bundy?

08:09.300 --> 08:11.300
You're married
to Big Red,

08:11.300 --> 08:14.300
the rich woman
with the sharp nails?

08:14.300 --> 08:15.801
Who are you?

08:15.801 --> 08:18.400
I'm an exotic dancer
at Troy's.

08:18.400 --> 08:19.400
Gee, that's great.

08:19.400 --> 08:20.868
Listen, I'd invite you in,
but instead,

08:20.868 --> 08:24.567
I'll just kick
the crap out of you.

08:24.567 --> 08:26.234
Oh, then perhaps
I'll just deliver

08:26.234 --> 08:27.567
my message and run.

08:27.567 --> 08:29.567
Your wife's friend,
Mrs. Rhoades,

08:29.567 --> 08:32.067
the one we call
"The Tentacle,"

08:32.067 --> 08:34.133
she lost her wedding
ring down my pants

08:34.133 --> 08:36.067
during the show last night,

08:36.067 --> 08:38.634
and I'm just
dropping it off to her.

08:44.100 --> 08:45.133
Come in.

08:52.968 --> 08:55.067
Raul, is it?

08:55.067 --> 08:57.667
Well, actually,
it's Wilbur.

08:57.667 --> 08:58.968
But I think I'm
too good-looking

08:58.968 --> 09:00.167
to be a Wilbur.

09:00.167 --> 09:01.667
Yeah, you betcha.

09:01.667 --> 09:03.667
Listen, exactly
what was Marcie doing

09:03.667 --> 09:06.734
when she lost
her ring down your, uh...

09:06.734 --> 09:08.467
underpants, was it?

09:08.467 --> 09:09.968
Yeah. She was tipping me.

09:09.968 --> 09:13.234
Could you see to it
that she gets this ring?

09:13.234 --> 09:15.767
As much as you believe
you're too good-looking

09:15.767 --> 09:17.868
to be a Wilbur,
believe she'll get it.

09:17.868 --> 09:19.367
Thanks, Mr. Bundy.

09:19.367 --> 09:20.801
Thank you, Raul.

09:20.801 --> 09:23.000
Oh, by the way, if my wife
should happen to lose

09:23.000 --> 09:24.033
anything down your pants,

09:24.033 --> 09:26.234
so will you.

09:29.767 --> 09:31.801
 <i>Hasta luego,</i>
Mr. Bundy.

09:31.801 --> 09:32.968
Right back at you.

09:37.267 --> 09:40.434
"To our everlasting love.
Steven."

09:40.434 --> 09:41.934
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

09:41.934 --> 09:45.801
Gee, I hope that's Steve.

09:45.801 --> 09:47.300
Hi, Steve.

09:47.300 --> 09:49.801
Hi, Al. Who's the guy
in the black Porsche?

09:49.801 --> 09:51.300
Santa Claus.

09:51.300 --> 09:52.801
Come on in.

09:52.801 --> 09:54.167
So Steve,
how's Marcie doing?

09:54.167 --> 09:56.934
Is she still mad
at you, buddy?

09:56.934 --> 09:58.467
Oh, I don't know.

09:58.467 --> 10:00.467
She said she forgave me,

10:00.467 --> 10:02.467
but I could tell
she was still tense.

10:02.467 --> 10:05.200
She just sat there
with her hands in her pockets,

10:05.200 --> 10:06.467
staring at the floor.

10:06.467 --> 10:08.534
I feel like dirt, Al.

10:08.534 --> 10:12.634
We'll get back to that later.

10:12.634 --> 10:16.067
But first, let me tell you
something about women.

10:16.067 --> 10:18.133
Uh-oh.

10:18.133 --> 10:19.434
See, women love us

10:19.434 --> 10:21.801
to look at them
like slabs of beef.

10:21.801 --> 10:24.734
You think they wear
those tight-fitting clothes

10:24.734 --> 10:26.734
just so some other
broad can say,

10:26.734 --> 10:30.467
"Gee, your hips
look succulent"?

10:30.467 --> 10:31.601
I mean, some do,

10:31.601 --> 10:32.601
but they become
gym teachers,

10:32.601 --> 10:35.300
and I'm talking
about women.

10:38.067 --> 10:39.767
I mean, let's
face it, Steve,

10:39.767 --> 10:41.934
until they get married,
they care how they look.

10:41.934 --> 10:43.200
But what else do they have?

10:43.200 --> 10:47.434
Brains? Wit? Ech.
Forget it.

10:47.434 --> 10:49.000
The good-looking ones
know we're looking.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.267
They love us
to be looking,

10:50.267 --> 10:51.701
and God bless them,

10:51.701 --> 10:55.834
they're carrying
the rest of their sex.

10:55.834 --> 10:59.734
Al, I'm an educated man.

10:59.734 --> 11:01.634
Don't you think
I know all that?

11:01.634 --> 11:03.300
It's just that
I feel so guilty.

11:03.300 --> 11:05.467
Every time I look
at Marcie's face,

11:05.467 --> 11:08.300
all I can see
is that girl's hiney.

11:08.300 --> 11:09.601
It's wrong, Al.

11:09.601 --> 11:12.067
I feel unworthy
of someone like Marcie.

11:12.067 --> 11:14.801
Yeah. She is
a special person.

11:14.801 --> 11:17.801
By the way,
here's her wedding ring

11:17.801 --> 11:20.801
that she lost down
some guy's jock

11:20.801 --> 11:22.334
at a strip club
last night.

11:26.834 --> 11:30.901
Anyway, how do you like
those Bears this year?

11:30.901 --> 11:32.701
Oh, wait a second, Al.

11:32.701 --> 11:33.834
What's this about

11:33.834 --> 11:35.801
Marcie losing
her wedding ring?

11:35.801 --> 11:37.300
Oh, yeah, yeah, here.

11:37.300 --> 11:40.300
Yeah, I got it
from the guy

11:40.300 --> 11:44.534
whose underpants
they were wedged in,

11:44.534 --> 11:46.534
but I wouldn't worry
about it, Steve.

11:46.534 --> 11:48.000
He's just some stripper
named Zorro,

11:48.000 --> 11:49.501
and I'm sure
it was nothing--

11:49.501 --> 11:50.901
you know, no affair
that was important

11:50.901 --> 11:52.133
or anything like that.

11:52.133 --> 11:53.534
In fact,
knowing Marcie as I do,

11:53.534 --> 11:56.033
she probably lost it
with dignity

11:56.033 --> 11:58.801
because as we all know,

11:58.801 --> 12:05.834
we're dirt
and she's evolved.

12:05.834 --> 12:07.634
I can't believe it.
My wife's wedding ring.

12:07.634 --> 12:09.801
Steve, if I thought
you were going to be upset,

12:09.801 --> 12:12.767
I never would've told you.

12:17.300 --> 12:20.300
What I'm giving you
there is a present.

12:20.300 --> 12:22.801
See, that's more
than a wedding ring.

12:22.801 --> 12:24.968
What you have there
is what I like to call

12:24.968 --> 12:26.300
a get-out-of-jail
free card.

12:26.300 --> 12:27.801
See, you can hold it,

12:27.801 --> 12:30.901
save it,
use it for anything.

12:30.901 --> 12:32.434
She's got all this,

12:32.434 --> 12:37.767
and she goes
to a strip joint?

12:37.767 --> 12:40.767
Hey, you could've knocked me
over with a feather.

12:40.767 --> 12:42.767
But getting back
to something more important--

12:42.767 --> 12:45.267
how do we make her pay?

12:45.267 --> 12:46.767
I got it.

12:46.767 --> 12:48.534
The next time she holds
one of those

12:48.534 --> 12:50.267
women's group meetings
over at her house,

12:50.267 --> 12:51.501
you stroll in, you say,

12:51.501 --> 12:54.267
"Hey, eight women in the house
and I got dirty dishes?"

12:54.267 --> 12:57.767
Let them get mad,
pat the ring in your pocket,

12:57.767 --> 13:02.767
make the mark
of the "Z."

13:02.767 --> 13:06.467
Al, I am going
to have a Stepford wife.

13:06.467 --> 13:07.968
Attaboy!

13:07.968 --> 13:10.634
Do me one favor.

13:10.634 --> 13:13.634
When you strip away
every ounce of humanity,

13:13.634 --> 13:16.133
every shred of pride
she has,

13:16.133 --> 13:19.634
just when she's bending down
to kiss your feet,

13:19.634 --> 13:22.133
tell her
you got the ring...

13:22.133 --> 13:23.667
from Al Bundy.

13:32.734 --> 13:37.234
Hey, I've done a good thing.

13:37.234 --> 13:39.434
I deserve a reward.

13:39.434 --> 13:43.367
 <i>And now, ladies,</i>
 <i>the shoe salesman!</i>

14:29.934 --> 14:31.834
[GARGLING]

15:02.934 --> 15:06.434
Hi, honey.
I was just going to tuck you in.

15:06.434 --> 15:08.868
Well, go ahead.

15:08.868 --> 15:11.400
I don't feel
like it anymore.

15:11.400 --> 15:17.400
Sit down,
sweetie puss.

15:17.400 --> 15:19.434
Honey...

15:19.434 --> 15:22.934
What's Troy's?

15:22.934 --> 15:24.434
Uh, well, uh...

15:24.434 --> 15:27.934
You know, it's this place
where I go with the girls,

15:27.934 --> 15:31.868
and we sit and swap recipes
and talk about the kids.

15:31.868 --> 15:34.734
And put dollar bills
down guys' underpants.

15:34.734 --> 15:37.234
Well, that too.
I'm going to turn in.

15:37.234 --> 15:39.334
It's a funny thing, Peg,
but the other day,

15:39.334 --> 15:41.200
I went to pay
the repairman,

15:41.200 --> 15:42.801
and when I looked
for my money--

15:42.801 --> 15:44.801
darned if every cent
wasn't gone.

15:44.801 --> 15:48.868
Oh, those kids!

15:48.868 --> 15:51.100
All right, Peg.

15:51.100 --> 15:54.634
Just how much of my money
has found its way

15:54.634 --> 15:57.501
into the crotches
of dancing, oily men?

15:57.501 --> 15:59.501
How would I know, Al?

15:59.501 --> 16:02.133
I don't count it,
I just shove it in.

16:04.901 --> 16:06.400
Well, that's that, then.

16:06.400 --> 16:08.901
Oh, uh, Big Red...

16:08.901 --> 16:12.400
you know,
I've been thinking.

16:12.400 --> 16:14.400
Remember
about a month ago,

16:14.400 --> 16:20.400
one night you came back
from swapping recipes...

16:20.400 --> 16:22.400
strangely,
how could I say,

16:22.400 --> 16:28.434
horny as a toad.

16:28.434 --> 16:31.434
That day I gave you
some money

16:31.434 --> 16:34.434
to have the brakes
on my car fixed.

16:34.434 --> 16:40.434
Do I have any brakes
on my car, Peg?

16:40.434 --> 16:41.834
No, Al.

16:43.934 --> 16:45.434
And remember you told me

16:45.434 --> 16:48.434
that the kids needed money
for a school project?

16:48.434 --> 16:51.167
We don't really sponsor
a Korean family, do we, Peg?

16:54.434 --> 16:56.334
No, Al.

16:56.334 --> 16:57.934
And Kelly's
contact lenses?

16:57.934 --> 16:59.467
Uh...

16:59.467 --> 17:02.467
So the big frost
didn't really drive up

17:02.467 --> 17:03.968
the price of Tang?

17:03.968 --> 17:07.467
But we still do have
the Bundy funeral plot?

17:07.467 --> 17:10.467
Um...

17:10.467 --> 17:12.968
Well, how about
the kids, Peg?

17:12.968 --> 17:15.968
Did they really go
to your mother's house,

17:15.968 --> 17:18.733
or do they belong
to Arabs now?

17:20.467 --> 17:21.968
That really hurts, Al.

17:21.968 --> 17:24.467
I can't believe
you don't trust me.

17:24.467 --> 17:25.968
Okay, Peg.

17:25.968 --> 17:29.467
From now on, I want your
shopping receipts notarized.

17:29.467 --> 17:33.501
From now on, I check eyes,
teeth, vet bills, school books.

17:33.501 --> 17:35.634
Oh, and you know
our joint checking account?

17:35.634 --> 17:37.834
I want to know
what bank it's in.

17:42.000 --> 17:44.400
Well, in my defense, Al,

17:44.400 --> 17:47.334
these are superb men.

17:47.334 --> 17:48.901
Don't push it, Peg.

17:48.901 --> 17:50.400
Now, I'm going to bed.

17:50.400 --> 17:53.901
I don't want you ever
going to Troy'sagain.

17:53.901 --> 17:57.100
From now on, you
and Troy'sare history.

18:04.901 --> 18:07.801
Good night, Al.

18:13.934 --> 18:14.934
Al--

18:14.934 --> 18:16.801
No!

18:25.934 --> 18:29.267
* Da da da
Da da dum *

18:29.267 --> 18:32.434
* Da da ta ta *

18:32.434 --> 18:35.434
* Dum dum dum *

18:35.434 --> 18:38.133
* Dum dum dum *

18:38.133 --> 18:42.901
* Dum **

18:42.901 --> 18:48.167
Al, your breakfast
is almost ready.

18:51.901 --> 18:54.000
Hey, is everybody happy?

18:54.000 --> 18:57.400
Oh, yes, yes, yes!

18:57.400 --> 18:58.901
Oh, God, yes!

18:58.901 --> 19:00.334
What a dad!

19:14.934 --> 19:17.801
I don't want you thinking
about Troy's,either.

19:21.434 --> 19:22.801
Yes, dear.

19:31.267 --> 19:32.767
No, Marcie,

19:32.767 --> 19:34.934
I don't think the floor
is clean enough.

19:34.934 --> 19:38.434
Wash it again...
with your hair.

19:38.434 --> 19:40.300
MARCIE:
Steve, I'm home.

19:48.434 --> 19:49.434
Hi.

19:49.434 --> 19:51.434
Hi. Where have
you been?

19:51.434 --> 19:52.934
Out shopping with Peg.

19:52.934 --> 19:55.934
Gee, that's
the second night in a row

19:55.934 --> 19:57.133
you've been out
with Peggy.

19:57.133 --> 19:59.267
Oh, well, I guess
you're a good example for her.

19:59.267 --> 20:02.934
Hmm? Oh, well,
I try to be.

20:02.934 --> 20:04.567
You know, Steve, I think

20:04.567 --> 20:07.434
I've been too hard on you
these past two days.

20:07.434 --> 20:08.934
Oh?

20:08.934 --> 20:10.434
Yes. I mean,
there's nothing wrong

20:10.434 --> 20:12.934
with looking at
another human being

20:12.934 --> 20:14.434
and appreciating
their form.

20:14.434 --> 20:15.934
Oh?

20:15.934 --> 20:18.968
Yes. I mean, I was wrong
to yell at you

20:18.968 --> 20:20.968
for looking
at that girl.

20:20.968 --> 20:22.467
So you forgive me?

20:22.467 --> 20:23.968
That's big of you.

20:23.968 --> 20:26.434
Oh, Steven...

20:26.434 --> 20:28.000
you're the most
wonderful husband

20:28.000 --> 20:29.434
in the world.

20:29.434 --> 20:30.801
I'm the one

20:30.801 --> 20:32.434
who should
apologize to you.

20:32.434 --> 20:33.801
There's nothing wrong

20:33.801 --> 20:35.434
with a little
physical attraction.

20:35.434 --> 20:36.567
After all, that's

20:36.567 --> 20:38.868
what first attracted
me to you.

20:38.868 --> 20:40.267
Well, I guess I am
sort of

20:40.267 --> 20:44.367
the whole
ball of wax.

20:44.367 --> 20:49.367
I remember the first
time I saw you,

20:49.367 --> 20:53.901
running that marathon.

20:53.901 --> 20:55.400
Your arms were tense,

20:55.400 --> 20:57.400
your chest was heaving.

20:57.400 --> 20:59.901
there were tears
in your eyes,

20:59.901 --> 21:02.400
but still
you tried to catch

21:02.400 --> 21:04.400
that woman in the lead.

21:04.400 --> 21:06.400
I love you, Steve.

21:06.400 --> 21:08.400
Do you forgive me?

21:08.400 --> 21:10.400
Of course I do.

21:10.400 --> 21:12.901
Oh! Um...
this came for you.

21:12.901 --> 21:16.400
Somebody dropped
it off at Al's.

21:16.400 --> 21:18.334
What is it?

21:22.901 --> 21:24.400
I don't know.

21:24.400 --> 21:26.367
It was for you.

21:37.100 --> 21:38.968
MARCIE:
All right!

21:42.767 --> 21:46.801
[TOILET FLUSHES]

21:49.801 --> 21:51.934
So what was it?

21:51.934 --> 21:54.901
Oh... coupons.

21:54.901 --> 21:56.400
From Peg.

21:56.400 --> 21:58.434
So I tore them up in little bits

21:58.434 --> 22:00.434
and flushed them
down the toilet.

22:00.434 --> 22:01.934
I love you, Steve.

22:04.434 --> 22:06.334
I love you, Marcie.

22:25.501 --> 22:29.367
So you lost your ring
down Zorro's pants, huh?

